
1) OpRegions are created with geoview (moos-ivp)

  $ geoview athens_hgoo_20.tif

Four regions were created:

OPA1="28.4,16.7:35.4,28.2:11,42.5:3.6,30.8"
OPA2="28.4,16.7:38.4,33.4:27.6,52.2:-0.4,58:-12.3,40.1"
OPA3="28.4,16.7:38.4,33.4:39,56:21.2,67.8:-7.8,67.9:-25.5,47.5"
OPA4="28.4,16.7:38.4,33.4:42.8,61.5:29,89.1:-9,91.5:-34.9,52.8"


2) Swim files are created with gen_swimmers (moos-ivp-2680)

  $ gen_swimmers --poly="28.4,16.7:35.4,28.2:11,42.5:3.6,30.8"
                 --sep=5 > athens_00.txt

  In fact, the build_swim_files.sh script builds a random laydown
  for five files:

  athens_00.txt  (region 1, smallest)
  athens_01.txt  (region 1)
  athens_02.txt  (region 2)
  athens_03.txt  (region 3)
  athens_04.txt  (region 4, largest)

3) The swim files can be viewed with swimview (moos-ivp-2680)

  $ cd rescue_athens
  $ swimview athens_*.txt

  Use the ']' and '[' keys to cycle through the swim files.

4) To launch the mission

  $ ./launch.sh 5 -r1

  This will launch the mission warp 5, single vehicle rescue
  mission (r1), and swimfile athens_00.txt by default.

  $ ./launch.sh 5 -r2 --rand


Note: When making a random swim_file at launch time, the file
is created into athens_rand.txt and then loaded..
